<h1>Glas3 concepts: Array</h1>
A <b>Matrix</b> is a <a href="FixedOrderArray">FixedOrderArray</a> of order two, i.e., a matrix.
<h2>Requirements</h2>
The type <code>X</code> satisfies Array if and only if:
<ul>
<li><code>X</code> satisfies <a href="FixedOrderArray">FixedOrderArray</a>.
</li>
<li><code>X</code> must have the following static value:
<table border="1">
<tr><th>name</th><th>type</th><th>notes</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>fixed_order</code></td><td><code>int</td><td><code>X::fixed_order==2</code></tr>
</table>
</li>
<li>Given
<ul>
<li><code>x</code> of type <code>X</code>
</ul>
the following expressions must be valid and have their specified effects:
<table border="1">
<tr><th>Expression</th><th>Return type</th><th>Semantics</th><th>conditions</th></tr>
<tr>
<td><code>x.num_rows()</code></td><td><code>X::size_type::value_type</code></td>
<td>Return the number of rows of the matrix</td><td>NEEDED?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>x.num_columns()</code></td><td><code>X::size_type::value_type</code></td>
<td>Return the number of columns of the matrix</td><td>NEEDED?</td>
</tr>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>Matrix in Glas3</h2>
